The leading aspirant of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Edo State, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu, has announced the appointment of three political leaders in the state into his Campaign Organisation, a move that is indicative of his strong support within the party. This is expected to strengthen his lead ahead of the primary election slated for June 22. Among those appointed are Mr. Ehiogie West-Idahosa, a three-term member of the House of Representatives and former Chairman of House Committee on Petroleum Matter; Mr. Samson Osagie, former Minority Whip of the House of Representatives and Mr. Patrick Ikhariale, a former member of the House of Representatives and Chairman of the House Committee on Power. A statement issued reads: “They have all been appointed into the Osagie Ize-Iyamu Campaign Organization.” Announcing the appointments and specifying the roles of the appointees, Mr. John Mayaki, the Director of Communication and Media of the Campaign Organization, said in a statement that “ today, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu directed the appointment of three eminent Edo leaders, Ehiogie West-Idahosa, Mr. Samson Osagie, and Patrick Ikhariale, into the Campaign Organization.” “The appointments which takes immediate effect, is to strengthen the operations of the Campaign Organization as we anticipate the primary election of our great party, the All Progressives Congress, on the 22nd of June. “All three leaders who are well-respected and enjoy great influence within the state and beyond will bring to bear their already demonstrated extraordinary leadership and strong character.” 